    <string name="help_title_configurations">Help: Configurations</string>
    <string name="help_configurations">Tap on the \'+\' icon to create a new configuration.
                        A configuration defines the TRS-80 model and the disk images used for
                        the emulation. Click on a configuration to run the emulator. Long-press
                        on a configuration for further options.
                        Note that currently only Model I and Model III emulation is supported.</string>
    <string name="help_title_edit_configuration">Help: Edit Configuration</string>
    <string name="help_edit_configuration">A configuration defines the parameters used by the
                        emulator. Select the TRS-80 model to emulate.
                        Note that currently only Model I and Model III emulation is supported.
                        If no disk images are defined,
                        the TRS-80 ROM will launch the Basic interpreter. Disk images need to be
                        copied to the SD card. This app does not contain disk images for copyright
                        reasons. You can search the Internet for
                        \'<a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=trs-80+disk+images">TRS-80 disk
                        images</a>\'.
                        A default blank cassette tape is created for each new configuration.
                        A different file can be mounted as the cassette image file.
                        Different keyboard types can be configured for portrait and landscape
                        orientation. The original keyboard mimics the layout of the TRS-80
                        keyboard. The compact layout is appropriate for smaller screen sizes.
                        The gaming layout offers a joystick control.
                        The tilt interface uses the accelerometer to control the cursor keys.
                        Touching the screen anywhere triggers the SPACE key.</string>
    <string name="help_title_settings">Help: Settings</string>
    <string name="help_settings">The emulator requires the original ROM images of the
                        various TRS-80 models. ROM images for the TRS-80 need to be copied
                        to the SD card before using this app.
                        For copyright reasons this app does not bundle ROM images. You can find
                        them on the Internet (for example
                        <a href="http://www.classiccmp.org/cpmarchives/trs80/Miscellany/Emulatrs/trs80-62/">here</a>).</string>

